parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission lock-up can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop moving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission "locks up" and the vehicle will no longer move
the rear wheel will not turn
the vehicle makes a chattering noise
the noise gets louder when shifting gears
the vehicle skids to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Reverse Gear Engagement While in Motion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected engagement of the reverse gear while in motion can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The reverse gear engages while the vehicle is in motion
the vehicle starts whining or engaging
the "R" light illuminates
the vehicle slows down or stops suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission gear skipping or clunking can cause loss of power, sudden skidding, or accidents, especially when accelerating or cornering.
symptoms: The transmission makes a loud clunking noise when shifting gears
the vehicle skips a gear dog
the transmission hesitates or slips
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ineffectiveness of the rear brakes can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to stop, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially in panic situations.
symptoms: The rear brakes require pumping to engage
the rear brakes are slow to respond
the rear brakes are ineffective
the vehicle hesitates or fails to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The radiator overflow tank's location and design make it prone to damage from road debris, which can cause coolant leakage, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Coolant leakage
coolant spill on the roadway
damage to the radiator overflow tank
risk of accidents or injuries due to loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fracture of the motorcycle's frame can lead to a loss of structural integrity, affecting the vehicle's handling and stability, and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Cracks or fractures appear on the passenger and driver side lower frame
particularly near the passenger side footrest.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Engine Control Module (ECM) Causing Engine Stalling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty ECM can cause the engine to stall while driving, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies while driving
especially when the engine is warm
the vehicle loses power
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle may experience difficulty starting or may not start at all.
